User
Create a basic HTML structure for the ProConnect platform with a header, main content area, and footer.

Header:
- Include a navigation bar with links to different sections of the platform such as Home, Profile, Connections, Messages, etc.
- Add a logo or brand name for ProConnect on the left side of the navigation bar.
- Use semantic HTML elements for accessibility and SEO benefits.

Main Content Area:
- Divide the main content area into sections for displaying newsfeed updates, user profile information, search bar, etc.
- Include placeholders for dynamic content that will be populated by JavaScript or server-side scripting.
- Use appropriate HTML elements and classes to structure the content and apply styling later with CSS.

Footer:
- Create a footer section containing copyright information, links to terms of service, privacy policy, and contact information.
- Optionally, include social media icons or links to ProConnect's social media profiles.

Ensure the HTML structure is well-organized, semantically meaningful, and easy to maintain.
Here's a basic HTML structure for the ProConnect platform:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>ProConnect</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css"> <!-- Link to CSS file for styling -->
</head>
<body>

  <!-- Header -->
  <header>
    <div class="logo">
      <a href="index.html">ProConnect</a>
    </div>
    <nav>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="index.html">Home</a></li>
        <li><a href="profile.html">Profile</a></li>
        <li><a href="connections.html">Connections</a></li>
        <li><a href="messages.html">Messages</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
  </header>

  <!-- Main Content Area -->
  <main>
    <!-- Newsfeed Section -->
    <section class="newsfeed">
      <h2>Newsfeed</h2>
      <!-- Placeholder for newsfeed updates -->
      <div class="newsfeed-updates">
        <!-- Dynamic content will be added here -->
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- User Profile Section -->
    <section class="profile">
      <h2>User Profile</h2>
      <!-- Placeholder for user profile information -->
      <div class="profile-info">
        <!-- Dynamic content will be added here -->
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Search Bar Section -->
    <section class="search">
      <h2>Search</h2>
      <!-- Placeholder for search bar -->
      <div class="search-bar">
        <!-- Dynamic content will be added here -->
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <!-- Footer -->
  <footer>
    <div class="copyright">
      &copy; 2024 ProConnect. All rights reserved.
    </div>
    <nav>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="terms.html">Terms of Service</a></li>
        <li><a href="privacy.html">Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="contact.html">Contact</a></li>
      </ul>
    </nav>
    <!-- Optionally, include social media icons or links -->
  </footer>

</body>
</html>
This HTML structure includes a header with a navigation bar, a main content area divided into sections for newsfeed updates, user profile information, and a search bar, and a footer containing copyright information and links to terms of service, privacy policy, and contact information. It also uses semantic HTML elements for better accessibility and SEO.

